annotations.comment:
Shuttleworthia satelles (There is no 16S rDNA gene available at
this time) is a member of the Firmicutes division of the domain
bacteria and has been isolated from the oral cavity. The sequenced
strain was obtained from Floyd E. Dewhirst and Jacques Izard who
acquired the sample from the Deutsche Sammlung von Mikroorganismen
und Zellkulturen GmbH (DSMZ) (DSM 14600).
We have performed one round of automated sequence improvement
(pre-finishing), along with manual improvement that includes
breaking apart any mis-assembly, and making manual joins where
possible. Manual edits also are made where the consensus appears to
be incorrect. All low quality data on the ends of contigs is
removed. Contigs are ordered and oriented where possible.
This work was supported by the National Human Genome Research
Institute and the NIH Roadmap Human Microbiome Project
[http://nihroadmap.nih.gov/hmp/].
This is a reference genome for the Human Microbiome Project. This
project is co-owned with the Human Microbiome Project DACC.
Genome Coverage:  35X
Sequencing Technology: 454.
